title: 6.4 Magnitude Earthquake Topples Buildings In Taiwan

json.text: Multiple news outlets report a 6.4 magnitude earthquake in Hualien, Taiwan, toppled buildings
Part of a hotel reportedly collapsed, and emergency crews are working to rescue dozens
The U.S. Geological Survey says the earthquake had very strong perceived shaking and moderate
Photos posted on social media show damage to buildings and massive cracks in roads.
There's no word yet on injuries.
